<paragraph blockId="96.[189,1399,1628,1726]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,617,1628,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procera" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Eucartosyrphus">
<emphasis box="[189,302,1628,1654]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[320,506,1628,1654]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Eucartosyrphus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[525,617,1629,1654]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[626,718,1629,1655]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares the following characters with other species of the subgenus: eye bare, antennal pits confluent, scutum with long, black bristles and the structure of the male genitalia. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[304,514,1700,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procera" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[304,514,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Cheilosia procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[520,610,1700,1726]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the only species of subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[978,1164,1700,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Eucartosyrphus">
<emphasis box="[978,1164,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Eucartosyrphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1321,1395,1700,1726]" name="Nepal" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Nepal</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1399,1766,1840]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="96.[189,324,1766,1792]" box="[189,324,1766,1792]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1766,1792]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1766,1792]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[189,1399,1813,1840]" box="[189,1399,1813,1840]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[637,740,1814,1839]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">procerus</emphasis>
ʼ, meaning ‘longʼ, referring to the habitus of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
